      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يَقُولُ لِلرَّجُلِ أَبْتَاعُ لَكَ مَتَاعاً وَ اَلرِّبْحُ بَيْنِي وَ بَيْنَكَ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3793 - Asim bin Humayd narrated from Abu Basir:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a man who says to another man, \"I will buy merchandise for you, and the profit will be shared between me and you.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
